<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="feature-n">feature <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'fiːtʃə(r)/    美 /'fiːtʃər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>特征；特点</strong></h4>
<p>an important or noticeable part of sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>An important feature of Van Gogh's paintings is their bright colors.
梵高画作的一个重要特征是色彩鲜亮。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This city has no particular <strong>distinguishing features</strong>.
这座城市没有明显的特点。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>面貌的一部分 (指眼、口、鼻等)；面貌 (特征)</strong></h4>
<p>a part of sb's face：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>have nice features
容貌姣好</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her eyes are her best feature.
她五官中眼睛最好看。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(报纸、杂志等的) 特写；专题节目</strong></h4>
<p>a special article or programme about sb / sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She showed great interest in a special <strong>feature on</strong> education in today's newspaper.
她对今天报纸上一个关于教育的专栏特别感兴趣。</p></div></div>